4:
Oh, Ms. Sprite User! I saw your
performance the other day! What a
show!
8: Ah, I see! Um... Thank you very much!
12:
Looks like someone's popular. You're
the talk of the Guild too, right?
16:
Y-yes! Since then, I've been given a
number of jobs related to sprites...
21:
Hehe, you're keeping me busy as
well.
25:
Ah... I'm sorry about that... There are
all sorts of festivities going on, yet
you have to watch me.
29:
Fret not, Lady Phiria. I am enjoying
myself all the same.
32: Well, look who it is! Perfect timing!
35:
What is it, sir? ...Ah, don't tell me it
happened again.
38:
Oh, no, our sprite user is as healthy
as a horse now! They were able to
get plenty of bed rest thanks to you.
40:
I was actually looking for you for a
different reason.
47:
Y-you... want to make me a member
of your troupe?
50:
Well, it's hard to ignore a
performance like that.
51:
Everyone was amazed by your
powers. Even our own sprite user.
54:
Hmmm... Do you require an answer
right away?
57:
Of course not! We couldn't possibly
force your hand like that.
58:
We're not a traveling troupe, either,
so feel free to stop by any time.
61:
I see... What would you like to do,
Phiria?
65: I'll... need some time to think about it.
72:
What did you think? ...It was fun?
Hehe, is that so?
74:
I suppose it was. Practice was hard,
but there was a true sense of
accomplishment... It was strange.
77:
Sounds to me like it was a good
experience for you.
80:
This happened before, didn't it? It
seems I'm always interrupting your
time with the sprites.
84:
No, it's fine... I've been pacing around
this whole time, so I appreciate
having you here.
87:
I'm not... opposed to joining the
troupe. Rehearsal was tough, but it
was also fun...
92:
You need not worry about us. Just
do as you please. That's what others
in this town are doing.
99:
I thought I knew what my dream
was, but the minute I figured it out,
suddenly I couldn't move forward...
103:
I-isn't that strange? I'm able to fight
now, and my life is no longer in
danger, but
110:
There's no telling whether you have
what it takes, nor can we guarantee
that things will work out.
Nevertheless, we all continue to walk
down our own paths.
112:
Perhaps courage is what we truly
need.
119:
...I believe I only realized that after
coming to this village.
122:
Being nervous is natural. Moving
forward despite it is admirable, but
that doesn't make retreating
reproachable. Other opportunities
will present themselves.
124:
So if I had one piece of advice, I
would say...
127:
It's okay, Phiria. It's okay to have
regrets... No matter what, we'll be
there for you.
140:
I'm sorry. I wish to stay with these
people.
143:
You don't need to apologize! I had a
feeling you would reject our offer.
145:
That being said, I am a little
disappointed. I wanted to see what
kind of show you and our sprite user
would put on.
148:
A-actually, about that! If you don't
mind... Perhaps I could make a
suggestion...
154:
Um, how do I explain it... It depends
on how much you can actually talk
to the sprites... I-I think...
158:
I knew this would happen... There's
no way she can teach others like
that.
161:
Well, I'm sure with practice, she'll get
used to it... But I agree. She's not
ready to teach.
166:
Ah, Lady Phiria... If you say it like that,
their self-esteem will surely
174:
...I think you all might be a tad
overprotective of her too.
